Class IntLinkedListStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.PrimitiveCollection
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.list.store.PrimitiveListStore
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.list.store.IntLinkedListStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, Initializable, NamedObject, Countable, Sized, CompressibleCollection
    public class IntLinkedListStore
extends PrimitiveListStore
    Stores linked lists of int values in a space efficient way.

    The add(int, int) method takes a list identifier and adds the given value to the head of the list, returning an identifier to the new list. To start a new list, pass NEW_LIST as the list identifier. To retrieve the list as an IntIterator, call list(int) with the list identifier.

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    IntIterator, Quantizable
